1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Today's topic is the Shravagama Sutra.

2
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Buddha spoke the sutras to cause living beings to go back to the origin and to return to the source.

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:31,000
In other words, to turn our backs on the mundane life and to unite with enlightenment.

4
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:35,000
The Shravagama Sutra is known as the Sutra for Enlightenment.

5
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Today we will share a beautiful verse from the Sutra, hopefully to bring forth great wisdom.

6
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Ananda, you have not yet understood that all the defiling objects that appear,

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
all the illusory, ephemeral characteristics spring up in the very spot

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
where they also come to an end.

9
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Ananda is a main character of the Sutra.

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Once collecting alms, he was under the spell of the daughter of a mantamji.

11
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:11,000
As a monk for twelve years, he almost lost the sexual misconduct precept.

12
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Why did this happen to him? Because he did not understand the truth.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
The truth is that all is illusory and ephemeral.

14
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Our attraction between men and women is only an illusion of the mind.

15
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
It is short-lived and it is impermanent.

16
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Ananda did not see. He was still under the influence of the spell.

17
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:41,000
We need to see clearly the truth, where all the phenomena or delusions come from.

18
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:45,000
It springs up from the very spot where they also come to an end,

19
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:49,000
which means they come from nowhere and they go to nowhere.

20
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
The very spot is emptiness.

21
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:00,000
In the Tantide Buddhism, we use the three meditations to understand our one true mind.

22
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:07,000
The three meditations are Void Meditation, Unreal Meditation, and Ming Meditation.

23
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Void Meditation means understanding the true essence of all phenomena is emptiness.

24
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Unreal Meditation means to understand that everything

25
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
has conventional existence.

26
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:26,000
You cannot say they do not exist, but it's unreal existence.

27
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:32,000
So it's all because of cause and condition that they arise and cease.

28
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:39,000
Number three is the Ming Meditation, or one true mind, the middle way.

29
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:45,000
This whole sutra is talking about one mind in terms of the three meditations.

30
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,000
The first section is about Void Meditation.

31
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:55,000
All the phenomena only comes up at the very spot, which is emptiness.

32
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
In this sutra, it talks about a practitioner.

33
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:02,000
He's known as a pure youth adorned with fragrance.

34
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,000
His specialty is his sense of smell.

35
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
One time, they were lighting up incense.

36
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,000
He said, I contemplated this fragrance.

37
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
It did not come from the wood.

38
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
It did not come from emptiness.

39
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,000
It did not come from the smoke.

40
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,000
It did not come from the fire.

41
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,000
There's no place it came from, and there's no place it went to.

42
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Because of this, my discriminating mind dispelled, and I attained the absence of outflow.

43
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:40,000
So this practitioner, he was able to become enlightened through the sense of smell.

44
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Through this fragrance, he understands it's coming from nowhere.

45
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
It's not the wood.

46
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
It's not the empty sky.

47
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:51,000
It's not the fire or the smoke.

48
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,000
It comes from nowhere, and it goes nowhere.

49
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,000
It's emptiness.

50
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,000
It has no more outflow.

51
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,000
That means no more afflictions.

52
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:04,000
We can learn how to be enlightened and understand emptiness.

53
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:09,000
For example, if someone insulted us, we became angry.

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Where does this anger come from?

55
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
We have to contemplate.

56
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
It comes from nowhere, and it goes nowhere.

57
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Did it come from this person's words?

58
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:24,000
If it came from this person's words, then everybody should be upset when they hear it.

59
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
But only I'm upset.

60
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,000
That means it has no real existence.

61
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Is it coming from myself?

62
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
If it's coming from myself, then I should be angry all the time.

63
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,000
So it's not from myself either.

64
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
So there's nowhere it came from.

65
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,000
It's true nature.

66
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,000
It's emptiness.

67
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:47,000
That way, we can let go of this anger because this anger is not me.

68
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:53,000
I am the emptiness, which is our true nature, our true enlightened mind.

69
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Now let's look at the second line.

70
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:59,000
They are what is called illusory falseness.

71
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:03,000
This is talking about the unreal meditation.

72
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,000
They do look like they exist.

73
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Just like the shadow, you can see the shadow.

74
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,000
But do they really exist?

75
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:13,000
It's only a shadow.

76
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Like a magician pulling a rabbit out of the hat.

77
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Just like a hand.

78
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,000
So is it real?

79
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
It's an illusion.

80
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,000
So it exists.

81
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
It has conventional existence.

82
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:29,000
But it's only from karma, from cause and effect that everything springs up.

83
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
But it's all emptiness.

84
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,000
So understand the unreal nature of their existence.

85
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,000
But their nature is in truth the bright substance of wonderful enlightenment.

86
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
We understand emptiness.

87
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:48,000
We understand their conventional existence as illusory falseness.

88
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Then we will understand everything's true nature is the bright substance of wonderful enlightenment.

89
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Our one true mind.

90
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:05,000
So we should use this illusory life right now to match with our nature.

91
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
It's called the Dharma nature.

92
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Every urge.

93
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Every thought.

94
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:14,000
Every action should accord with the Dharma nature.

95
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:19,000
Then our great wisdom will emerge and afflictions will cease.

96
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Now we explain it further.

97
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Thus it is throughout up to the five skandhas, six entrances to the twelve places and the eighteen realms,

98
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:38,000
the union and mixture of various causes and conditions account for their illusory and false existence.

99
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:46,000
And the separation and dispersion of the causes and conditions results in their illusory and false extinction.

100
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
The first part is void meditation.

101
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,000
The second part is unreal meditation.

102
00:06:52,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Again, we call our body and mind the five skandhas of form, feelings, perception, mental formation and consciousness.

103
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,000
That consists our body and mind.

