00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,000
the five skandhas, they're all hindrances.

151
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:20,000
But if we go inward and contemplate on their true nature,

152
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:23,000
the five skandhas and the eighteen realms,

153
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,000
they're helping us to become enlightened.

154
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,000
In the sutra, it talks about two dharma principles.

155
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:34,000
Dharma princes named physician kings and superior physicians.

156
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:39,000
They became enlightened through the sensory object of the taste.

157
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,000
From the twelve places, they said,

158
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:47,000
the nature of flavor is not empty and non-existent,

159
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,000
nor is it the body and mind,

160
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:53,000
nor is it apart from the body and mind.

161
00:10:53,000 --> 00:10:58,000
We became enlightened by discriminating among flavors.

162
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:05,000
The flavor is not empty because it has unreal existence.

163
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:09,000
And it's non-existent because it's voidness.

164
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:12,000
It's not the body and mind.

